cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with analyzing the performance of a network with access points, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the achievable signal-to-interference-plus-noise ratio (SINR) and user capacity, which are concepts related to information theory.
3. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper deals with the distribution of access points in a finite area, which can be considered as a multiagent system.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the impact of access point density on the performance of a network, which can be analyzed using systems and control theory.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper may be relevant to multimedia applications that require high network capacity and performance.
